wiki_catalogs.name: Project Overview
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for the SHG Management System project overview. Explain the purpose of this Self Help Group management platform for women's financial cooperatives, its target audience (SHG leaders, members, administrators), and core value proposition. Document the system's role in managing member registration, savings tracking, loan disbursement, repayment monitoring, and financial reporting. Include the project's mission to digitize traditional SHG operations and improve financial inclusion. Provide an architectural overview showing how the frontend React application integrates with local data storage to deliver a complete management solution. Address the project's positioning in the fintech space for grassroots financial organizations.

wiki_catalogs.name: Member Data Model
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the Member entity in the SHG Management System. Document the Member interface with field definitions including member_id (unique identifier), name, age, village, phone, income, and join_date. Explain the data types, validation rules, and business constraints for each field. Detail the sample member data structure and demonstrate how member records are created, updated, and managed. Include member search and filtering capabilities, data integrity requirements, and integration patterns with other data models like savings and loans. Address member profile management, photo handling, and data lifecycle considerations.

wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create detailed documentation for input and form components in the SHG Management System. For each component, describe props/attributes, validation patterns, error handling, and integration with React Hook Form. Address form composition patterns, custom validation rules, and user experience considerations for financial data entry scenarios.

wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# SHG Management System - Comprehensive Project Analysis

## 1. Project Introduction

### Purpose Statement
The SHG Management System (Self Help Group Management) is a comprehensive web application designed to manage and track Self Help Groups (SHGs), particularly focusing on women's financial cooperatives in rural and semi-urban communities. The platform provides essential tools for managing member profiles, savings records, loan disbursement, repayment tracking, and financial reporting.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Financial Management**: Streamline savings collection, loan processing, and repayment tracking for SHG members
- **Data Visualization**: Provide real-time insights into group financial health through dashboards and reports
- **Accessibility**: Offer an intuitive interface for SHG leaders and members to manage financial activities
- **Automation**: Reduce manual paperwork and administrative overhead through digital solutions

### Target Audience
- SHG leaders and committee members
- Financial officers managing multiple SHGs
- Government officials overseeing microfinance initiatives
- Community development workers

## 2. Technical Architecture

### Component Breakdown
The application follows a modern React-based architecture with TypeScript for type safety and enhanced developer experience:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[App Root] --> B[React Router]
    B --> C[Layout Components]
    C --> D[Dashboard Layout]
    C --> E[Navigation Sidebar]
    C --> F[Top Bar]
    
    A --> G[Page Components]
    G --> H[Dashboard]
    G --> I[Members Management]
    G --> J[Savings Tracking]
    G --> K[Loan Management]
    G --> L[Repayment Monitoring]
    G --> M[Reports & Analytics]
    
    A --> N[UI Components]
    N --> O[Primitive Components]
    N --> P[Composite Components]
    
    A --> Q[Data Layer]
    Q --> R[Local Data Files]
    Q --> S[State Management]
    
    A --> T[State Management]
    T --> U[React Query]
    T --> V[Context Providers]
```

### Design Patterns
- **Component Composition Pattern**: Modular UI components built with Radix UI primitives
- **Data Flow Pattern**: Unidirectional data flow with centralized state management
- **Layout Pattern**: Consistent dashboard layout with sidebar navigation
- **Form Pattern**: React Hook Form with Zod validation for data integrity

### System Relationships
The application maintains clear separation between presentation, business logic, and data layers:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Interface] --> B[Component Layer]
    B --> C[Business Logic]
    C --> D[Data Layer]
    D --> E[Local Storage/Data Files]
    
    F[State Management] --> B
    G[Routing] --> B
    H[Validation] --> C
    
    I[External Dependencies] --> B
    I --> C
    I --> D
```

## 3. Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points
- **Application Bootstrap**: [`src/main.tsx`](src/main.tsx) - Initializes React DOM and renders the root component
- **Root Application**: [`src/App.tsx`](src/App.tsx) - Configures routing, state providers, and global UI elements
- **Build Configuration**: [`vite.config.ts`](vite.config.ts) - Vite build system configuration with React SWC plugin
- **Styling Configuration**: [`tailwind.config.ts`](tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind CSS configuration with custom design tokens

### Core Modules
- **Data Management**: [`src/data/`](src/data/) - Local data stores for members, savings, loans, and repayments
- **Component Library**: [`src/components/ui/`](src/components/ui/) - Reusable UI primitives built on Radix UI
- **Page Components**: [`src/pages/`](src/pages/) - Feature-specific page implementations
- **Layout Components**: [`src/components/`](src/components/) - Structural components (DashboardLayout, AppSidebar)

### Configuration Approach
- **Package Management**: [`package.json`](package.json) - Comprehensive dependency management with React 18, TypeScript, and modern tooling
- **TypeScript Configuration**: [`tsconfig.json`](tsconfig.json) - Strict type checking with modern ECMAScript features
- **Testing Setup**: [`vitest.config.ts`](vitest.config.ts) - Unit testing configuration with Vitest and React Testing Library

### External Dependencies
Key dependencies include:
- **React Ecosystem**: React 18.3.1, React Router DOM 6.30.1, React Hook Form 7.61.1
- **UI Framework**: Radix UI primitives, shadcn/ui components, Tailwind CSS 3.4.17
- **State Management**: @tanstack/react-query 5.83.0 for caching and data synchronization
- **Utilities**: Lucide React icons, date-fns for date manipulation, clsx/tailwind-merge for class composition

### Integration Points
- **State Management**: React Query for server-state management and caching
- **Form Handling**: React Hook Form with Zod validation schema
- **Date Handling**: date-fns for consistent date operations
- **Animation**: Tailwind CSS animations and transitions

### Component Relationship Diagrams

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[DashboardLayout] --> B[AppSidebar]
    A --> C[TopBar]
    A --> D[Main Content]
    
    B --> E[Navigation Items]
    B --> F[Collapsible State]
    
    G[Page Components] --> A
    H[UI Components] --> G
    I[Data Services] --> G
```

## 4. Key Features

### Functionality Overview
The system provides comprehensive financial management capabilities for Self Help Groups:

#### Core Features
- **Member Management**: Complete member profiles with personal details, contact information, and financial history
- **Savings Tracking**: Monthly savings collection with multiple payment modes (Cash, UPI, Bank Transfer)
- **Loan Management**: Loan disbursement tracking with EMI calculation and repayment schedules
- **Repayment Monitoring**: Real-time tracking of due dates, overdue amounts, and payment status
- **Financial Reporting**: Dashboard analytics showing group financial health indicators
- **Chatbot Integration**: AI-powered customer support for common queries

### Implementation Highlights
- **Dashboard Analytics**: [`src/pages/Dashboard.tsx`](src/pages/Dashboard.tsx) - Central hub displaying key metrics and quick actions
- **Responsive Design**: [`src/components/DashboardLayout.tsx`](src/components/DashboardLayout.tsx) - Flexible layout adapting to different screen sizes
- **Navigation System**: [`src/components/AppSidebar.tsx`](src/components/AppSidebar.tsx) - Collapsible sidebar with active state management
- **UI Component Library**: [`src/components/ui/button.tsx`](src/components/ui/button.tsx) - Extensible button component with multiple variants and sizes

### Feature Architecture Diagrams

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Landing
    Landing --> Login
    Login --> Dashboard
    Dashboard --> Members
    Dashboard --> Savings
    Dashboard --> Loans
    Dashboard --> Repayments
    Dashboard --> Reports
    Dashboard --> Chatbot
    
    Members --> MemberProfile
    MemberProfile --> Members
    
    Savings --> Dashboard
    Loans --> Dashboard
    Repayments --> Dashboard
    Reports --> Dashboard
    Chatbot --> Dashboard
```

## 5. Conclusion and Recommendations

### Project Architecture Summary
The SHG Management System demonstrates a well-structured modern web application with clear architectural boundaries. The project successfully combines contemporary frontend technologies (React 18, TypeScript, Vite) with practical business logic for financial management. The modular component architecture ensures maintainability and scalability.

### Key Characteristics
- **Type Safety**: Comprehensive TypeScript implementation with strict type checking
- **Modern Tooling**: Vite build system with React SWC compiler for optimal performance
- **Design System**: Consistent UI components built on Radix UI primitives
- **State Management**: Efficient caching and synchronization with React Query
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with adaptive layouts

### Architectural Strengths
- Clear separation of concerns between UI, business logic, and data layers
- Extensible component library with consistent design tokens
- Robust routing system with nested layouts
- Comprehensive form handling with validation
- Performance optimization through React Query caching

### Potential Improvement Areas
- **Authentication System**: Implement proper user authentication and authorization
- **Database Integration**: Replace local data files with a backend database
- **Real-time Updates**: Add WebSocket support for live data synchronization
- **Export Functionality**: Implement CSV/PDF export for reports and member data
- **Mobile App**: Consider React Native implementation for offline functionality

### Actionable Recommendations
1. **Implement Authentication**: Add user login/logout functionality with role-based access control
2. **Database Migration**: Integrate with MongoDB or PostgreSQL for persistent data storage
3. **Performance Optimization**: Implement lazy loading for large datasets and optimize bundle size
4. **Testing Coverage**: Expand unit and integration test coverage beyond existing examples
5. **Accessibility**: Enhance accessibility compliance with WCAG guidelines

### Next Steps for Project Evolution
- **Phase 1**: User authentication and authorization system
- **Phase 2**: Backend API development with RESTful endpoints
- **Phase 3**: Real-time features with WebSocket integration
- **Phase 4**: Mobile application development
- **Phase 5**: Multi-language support and internationalization

Sources:
- [package.json](package.json)
- [App.tsx](src/App.tsx)
- [main.tsx](src/main.tsx)
- [tailwind.config.ts](tailwind.config.ts)
- [vite.config.ts](vite.config.ts)
- [Dashboard.tsx](src/pages/Dashboard.tsx)
- [members.ts](src/data/members.ts)
- [savings.ts](src/data/savings.ts)
- [DashboardLayout.tsx](src/components/DashboardLayout.tsx)
- [AppSidebar.tsx](src/components/AppSidebar.tsx)
- [button.tsx](src/components/ui/button.tsx)
- [utils.ts](src/lib/utils.ts)

</blog>
